    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank 13</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine Vareth. 
{SCRIPT: Node 13 displays if player has ITM_RINGA_ShadowRingVareth}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine Vareth again. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank 16</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine Areph. 
{SCRIPT: Node 16 displays if player has ITM_RINGA_ShadowRingAreph}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine Areph again. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>Put the rings away.
{SCRIPT: Only displays if PC has both of the ring pieces.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>Combine Areph and Vareth. 
{SCRIPT: Node only displays if player has both rings.}
{SCRIPT: Temporary node. Putting the rings together is not possible in Beta. Up to you whether we tell the player this.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>Pinching the rings between thumbs and forefinger, you struggle to bring them together. The force repelling them is not magnetism - it's almost as if someone is holding your hands apart with impossible, contemptuous strength. 

Nevertheless, there must be a way to join these rings. You just haven't found it yet. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>You hold Vareth to your eye. Upon close inspection, you see the minute twinkles of light upon tiny, incredibly sharp teeth along the rim. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>You gingerly lift Vareth to your eye again. The tiny teeth along the rim glitter.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>You hold the ring in one hand, though it seems like this should be impossible. The small thing is incredibly heavy. 

Small indentations trace the edge of the band. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Small indentations - like bite marks - line the edge of this incredibly heavy ring. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>You pull the first ring from your bags. At first, it looks like you've misplaced the second. Then, you find it pressed into a fold at the exact opposite end from where you found the first one. 

You reach down to grab it, but find that you can't - the rings reject each other with a force beyond magnetism alone. You pick up the second one with your other hand, and hold them in opposing palms. 

{SCRIPT: This conversation is no longer accessible once the player successfully joins the rings.}
{SCRIPT: Player has both rings, but hasn't combined them. Node 1, 3, and 4 are disabled once player has both rings.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>You weigh the other ring in your hand, teeth grazing your lip. The rings feel like they should match somehow. That they should be joined.
{SCRIPT: Player has both rings.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
